Name: Hope Mask
Description:
Armor crafted specifically for
members of the expedition.
The mask keeps the sand out.

Name: Hope Mail
Description:
Armor crafted specifically for
members of the expedition. An
all-seasons design for any clime.

Name: Hope Vambraces
Description:
Armor crafted specifically for
members of the expedition.
Pliant fingers help with
precision work.

Name: Hope Coil
Description:
Armor crafted specifically for
members of the expedition.
It is optimized for quick access.

Name: Hope Greaves
Description:
Armor crafted specifically for
members of the expedition. It
can handle nearly any terrain.

Name: Leather Headgear
Description:
Head armor made of treated
monster hide. A safe choice,
designed for multi-purpose use.

Name: Leather Vest
Description:
Simple chest armor reinforced
with monster hide. A design
that maximizes wearability.

Name: Leather Gloves
Description:
Armguards reinforced with
monster hide. They're light,
but provide ample protection.

Name: Leather Belt
Description:
Waistgear reinforced with
monster hide. Hunters swear by
its no-nonsense functionality.

Name: Leather Pants
Description:
Leg armor reinforced with
monster hide. Molds to the
body with extended use.

Name: Chainmail Headgear
Description:
Head armor made of woven chain
links. Its familiar design inspires
trust in hunters who wear it.

Name: Chainmail Vest
Description:
Chest armor made of woven chain
links. Tried and true, it offers
solid, functional defense.

Name: Chainmail Gloves
Description:
Armguards made of woven chain
links. They're easy to use and
a breeze to maintain.

Name: Chainmail Belt
Description:
Waistgear made of woven chain
links. A smart combination of
materials keeps it extra light.

Name: Chainmail Pants
Description:
Leg armor made of woven chain
links. The clever weave prevents
it from impairing movement.

Name: Bone Helm
Description:
Traditional head armor crafted
from monster bones. Believe it
or not, it offers pretty good
insulation.

Name: Bone Mail
Description:
Traditional chest armor with a
unique plating of intricately
pieced together monster bones.

Name: Bone Vambraces
Description:
Traditional armguards made
from monster bones. It's a
wonder these mismatched
shapes fit together.

Name: Bone Coil
Description:
Traditional waistgear bound
with monster bones. Looks
crude, but it does the job.

Name: Bone Greaves
Description:
Traditional leg armor crafted
from monster bones so light it's
like wearing nothing at all.

Name: Bulaqchi Specs
Description:
Spectacles made from Bulaqchi
parts. The hottest new design
for the stylish hunter.

Name: Talioth Vambraces
Description:
Talioth armguards. The forearm
blades are a classic example
of style over practicality.

Name: Chatacabra Helm
Description:
Chatacabra head armor.
The design is specially tailored
for desert hunting.

Name: Chatacabra Mail
Description:
Chatacabra chest armor.
Equipped with generous elastic
cushioning in the collar.

Name: Chatacabra Vambraces
Description:
Chatacabra armguards. They
protect the wrists without
hampering weapon handling.

Name: Chatacabra Coil
Description:
Chatacabra waistgear. The
charming, heart-shaped pouch
is made from its ample tongue.

Name: Chatacabra Greaves
Description:
Leg armor made from
Chatacabra spoils. A loose
fit for maximum mobility.

Name: Quematrice Helm
Description:
Head armor made from Quematrice
spoils. The shock of feathers
ties the whole look together.

Name: Quematrice Mail
Description:
Quematrice chest armor. The
design may look ceremonial,
but it offers ample protection.

Name: Quematrice Braces
Description:
Armguards made from Quematrice
parts. The wide cuffs allow
the wrists to move unimpeded.

Name: Quematrice Coil
Description:
Flaunt-worthy Quematrice
waistgear. Nothing shouts haute
couture like flowing tassets.

Name: Quematrice Greaves
Description:
Quematrice leg armor. The
ornate gaiters let a hunter
strut like a Quematrice.

Name: Alloy Helm
Description:
A helmet crafted from quality
ore. While it doesn't look like
much, this is highly functional
armor.

Name: Alloy Mail
Description:
Chest armor crafted from
quality ore. Made with a
logical, no-frills construction
that puts mobility first.

Name: Alloy Vambraces
Description:
Armguards crafted from quality
ore. Every element is streamlined
for maximum utility.

Name: Alloy Coil
Description:
Waistgear crafted from quality
ore. The complexly shaded patina
and sleek design are quite
stunning.

Name: Alloy Greaves
Description:
Leg armor crafted from quality
ore. What it lacks in charm it
more than makes up in defense.

Name: Piragill Greaves
Description:
Piragill leg armor. A light,
skintight fit made with the most
exquisite, buttery-soft leather.

Name: Vespoid Helm
Description:
A Vespoid helmet. The carapace
material is susceptible to fire
but offers sturdy coverage.

Name: Vespoid Mail
Description:
Vespoid chest armor. Its arcane
build provides formidable
resistance to physical attacks.

Name: Vespoid Vambraces
Description:
Vespoid armguards. They are as
heavy as they look, but they
afford significant defense.

Name: Vespoid Coil
Description:
Vespoid waistgear. The design
arose from the study of highly
defensive exoskeletons.

Name: Vespoid Greaves
Description:
Leg armor made from Vespoid
parts. Ingenious artisanship has
further reinforced the carapace.

Name: Barina Headgear
Description:
Lala Barina head armor. The
rose embellishments were
fashioned from its carapace.

Name: Barina Mail
Description:
Lala Barina chest armor. It may
look like normal clothing, but
it's just as hardy as armor.

Name: Barina Vambraces
Description:
Lala Barina armguards that
are so elegant they could
pass as formal wear.

Name: Barina Coil
Description:
Lala Barina waistgear that
nobility would gladly don
just to make an impression.

Name: Barina Greaves
Description:
Lala Barina leg armor. Pulls
the rose motif back in with
subtle but elegant detailing.

Name: Conga Helm
Description:
Head armor made from Congalala
materials. Remember: it's "feral,"
not "unkempt."

Name: Conga Mail
Description:
Chest armor made from Congalala
materials. The shocks of monster
fur help hunters keep it wild.

Name: Conga Vambraces
Description:
Armguards made from Congalala
materials. Crudely made but
highly protective.

Name: Conga Coil
Description:
Waistgear made from Congalala
materials, complete with an array
of handy pockets!

Name: Conga Greaves
Description:
Greaves made of Congalala parts.
Wild crafting perfect for those
who run in the wilderness.

Name: Balahara Helm
Description:
A Balahara helmet covered in
roughly polished protrusions
to strongly evoke its namesake.

Name: Balahara Mail
Description:
Balahara chest armor. The bulky
shoulders are roomy enough
to allow ample movement.

Name: Balahara Vambraces
Description:
Balahara armguards. The spikes
are arranged artfully in a way
that maximizes movement.

Name: Balahara Coil
Description:
Balahara waistgear. The fabric
is colored a shade of red that
stirs a competitive spirit.

Name: Balahara Greaves
Description:
Spiny Balahara leg armor.
The carapace has been split
into clever, fluid parts.

Name: Doshaguma Helm
Description:
Head armor made from Doshaguma
parts. Pity any enemy who dares
scoff at its imposing crest.

Name: Doshaguma Mail
Description:
Doshaguma chest armor. The
lush shocks of fur function as
a robust defensive layer.

Name: Doshaguma Braces
Description:
Doshaguma armguards. Teeming
with such feral power, they
had to be restrained with
metal bracers.

Name: Doshaguma Coil
Description:
Waistgear made from Doshaguma
parts. Nothing can muss the
thick pile of this sturdy sash.

Name: Doshaguma Greaves
Description:
Doshaguma leg armor. Whether
dune or sandstorm, nothing can
slow its wearer's progress.

Name: Duna Helm
Description:
Uth Duna head armor. The
plumage crafted from its
fins convey the forest's
will to the wearer.

Name: Duna Mail
Description:
Uth Duna chest armor. The tightly
fitted scales make the wearer feel
as if they are one with nature.

Name: Duna Vambraces
Description:
Uth Duna armguards. The rows
of stone beading are an elegant
touch that boosts concentration.

Name: Duna Coil
Description:
Uth Duna waistgear. The fabric
is imbued with the breath of the
forest, absorbing any impact.

Name: Duna Greaves
Description:
Elaborately patterned Uth Duna
leg armor. The design is said to
invoke the forest's protection.

Name: Ingot Helm
Description:
Head armor fashioned from
lustrous, golden ore. Regal
protection with a crown to
complete the look.

Name: Ingot Mail
Description:
Chest armor crafted from
brilliant golden ore. Its color and
design are both highly pleasing.

Name: Ingot Vambraces
Description:
Armguards fashioned from
lustrous, golden ore. A union
of artistry and utility with
no absence of durability.

Name: Ingot Coil
Description:
Waistgear fashioned from lustrous,
golden ore. It joins haute design
with the very latest in armor craft.

Name: Ingot Greaves
Description:
Leg armor fashioned from lustrous,
golden ore. Clever smithing makes
the metal feel fluid and light.

Name: Kranodath Mail
Description:
Kranodath chest armor. What
armor enthusiast could resist
such ornate plating?

Name: Rompopolo Helm
Description:
Rompopolo head armor.
The mask is needed to ward off
the material's residual toxins.

Name: Rompopolo Mail
Description:
Well-padded Rompopolo chest
armor. The fabric contains poison
that—supposedly—never leaks.

Name: Rompopolo Vambraces
Description:
Rompopolo armguards. The
poisonous needles in the claws
are neat, but tricky to use.

Name: Rompopolo Coil
Description:
Rompopolo waistgear fully
equipped with instruments
needed to handle poison.

Name: Rompopolo Greaves
Description:
Rompopolo leg armor. Careful
you don't accidentally lean on
those spare vials of poison...

Name: Rey Sandhelm
Description:
Rey Dau head armor. Its crest
reaches the heavens—proof that
this creature bows to no one.

Name: Rey Sandmail
Description:
Rey Dau chest armor. Its carapace
has been meticulously paneled
into a bastion of defense.

Name: Rey Sandbraces
Description:
Rey Dau armguards. A lingering
charge gives the wearer a grip
like a vice.

Name: Rey Sandcoil
Description:
Rey Dau waistgear. The
faintly glowing buckle
inspires awe and respect.

Name: Rey Sandgreaves
Description:
Rey Dau leg armor. A layer
of latent electricity cushions
blows and softens landings.

Name: Comaqchi Accessory
Description:
A Comaqchi head accessory.
The thin, sleek plating
emanates an eldritch gleam.

Name: Nerscylla Helm
Description:
A helmet made from Nerscylla
spoils. Protection this durable
requires masterful precision
and execution.

Name: Nerscylla Mail
Description:
Chest armor made from Nerscylla
materials. Advanced engineering
makes it feel impossibly light.

Name: Nerscylla Vambraces
Description:
Armguards made from Nerscylla
spoils. Extra play in the fingers
helps improve weapon handling.

Name: Nerscylla Coil
Description:
Waistgear made from Nerscylla
spoils. A work of art that exhibits
a deep dedication to armor craft.

Name: Nerscylla Greaves
Description:
Leg armor made from Nerscylla
spoils. It keeps hunters light
on their feet and looking good
in action.

Name: Hirabami Headdress
Description:
Head armor made from Hirabami
spoils. It keeps the wearer
attuned and bound to the wind
at all times.

Name: Hirabami Mail
Description:
Chest armor made from Hirabami
spoils. The style is inspired by the
gallant warriors of a foreign land.

Name: Hirabami Vambraces
Description:
Armguards made from Hirabami
spoils. Wind rises at the fingertips
in warning to all adversaries.

Name: Hirabami Coil
Description:
Waistgear made from Hirabami
spoils. The elegant sash harnesses
the wind to mitigate impacts.

Name: Hirabami Greaves
Description:
Leg armor made from Hirabami
spoils. Designed for mobility,
they feel like walking on wind.

Name: Ajarakan Helm
Description:
Imposing Ajarakan head armor.
Donning it will draw the fires
from within to burst forth.

Name: Ajarakan Mail
Description:
Ajarakan chest armor. The
heat of its flames warns prey
of their final immolation.

Name: Ajarakan Vambraces
Description:
Mighty Ajarakan armguards.
They have just as much
ground-shaking power
as their namesake.

Name: Ajarakan Coil
Description:
Ajarakan waistgear. It acts
as a tether to quell the
wearer's exploding rage.

Name: Ajarakan Greaves
Description:
Flame crested Ajarakan leg
armor. A heat so fierce that
each step makes the earth
shudder in agony.

Name: Udra Mirehelm
Description:
Nu Udra head armor. The world
through this mask is swathed
in vengeance and ebony fire.

Name: Udra Miremail
Description:
Nu Udra chest armor. As if a
curse manifested, tentacles drape
down to form a haunting cape.

Name: Udra Mirebraces
Description:
Chilling Nu Udra armguards.
They warp one's sense of
touch, changing warmth to
cold nothingness.

Name: Udra Mirecoil
Description:
Nu Udra waistgear. The gnash
of spikes and fangs are bound
by a personalized curse.

Name: Udra Miregreaves
Description:
Nu Udra leg armor. The wearer
could cross a sea of fire without
so much as a blister.

Name: G. Seikret Coil
Description:
Guardian Seikret waistgear.
The long, white feathers
produce a faint, exquisite glow.

Name: G. Doshaguma Helm
Description:
Head armor made from Guardian
Doshaguma spoils. To don it is
to be seized by unspeakable
cravings.

Name: G. Doshaguma Mail
Description:
Chest armor made from
Guardian Doshaguma spoils.
It instills a new vitality and
sense of purpose.

Name: G. Doshaguma Braces
Description:
Armguards made from Guardian
Doshaguma spoils. They agitate
the wearer unless in constant
motion.

Name: G. Doshaguma Coil
Description:
Waistgear made from Guardian
Doshaguma spoils. The white
areas self-repair when damaged.

Name: G. Doshaguma Greaves
Description:
Leg armor made from Guardian
Doshaguma spoils. Produces
a faint white aura when worn.

Name: G. Rathalos Helm
Description:
Head armor made from Guardian
Rathalos spoils. To don it is to be
seized by unspeakable cravings.

Name: G. Rathalos Mail
Description:
Chest armor made from Guardian
Rathalos spoils. It instills a new
vitality and sense of purpose.

Name: G. Rathalos Vambraces
Description:
Armguards made from Guardian
Rathalos spoils. They agitate the
wearer unless in constant motion.

Name: G. Rathalos Coil
Description:
Waistgear made from Guardian
Rathalos spoils. The white areas
self-repair when damaged.

Name: G. Rathalos Greaves
Description:
Leg armor made from Guardian
Rathalos spoils. Produces
a faint white aura when worn.

Name: G. Ebony Helm
Description:
Head armor made from Guardian
Ebony Odogaron spoils. To don it
is to be seized by unspeakable
cravings.

Name: G. Ebony Mail
Description:
Chest armor made from Guardian
Ebony Odogaron spoils. It
instills a new vitality and
sense of purpose.

Name: G. Ebony Braces
Description:
Armguards made from Guardian
Ebony Odogaron spoils. They
agitate the wearer unless in
constant motion.

Name: G. Ebony Coil
Description:
Waistgear made from Guardian
Ebony Odogaron spoils. The
white areas self-repair
when damaged.

Name: G. Ebony Greaves
Description:
Leg armor made from Guardian
Ebony Odogaron spoils. Produces
a faint white aura when worn.

Name: Xu Wu Helm
Description:
Concealing Xu Wu head armor.
Fitting attire for hunters who
dwell in darkness.

Name: Xu Wu Mail
Description:
Xu Wu chest armor. The long
scarf can be used as protective
gear and multi-purpose rope.

Name: Xu Wu Vambraces
Description:
Xu Wu armguards. The clever
design gives the wearer's fingers
a nimble edge even in the dark.

Name: Xu Wu Coil
Description:
Slinky Xu Wu waistgear. The
uniquely textured leather
moves silent as a whisper.

Name: Xu Wu Greaves
Description:
Xu Wu leg armor. Meticulously
crafted to allow the wearer to
slink silently through the dark.

Name: G. Arkveld Helm
Description:
Guardian Arkveld head armor.
A host of heightened senses
make up for the narrow view.

Name: G. Arkveld Mail
Description:
Guardian Arkveld chest armor.
It beckons forth a shudder of
indescribable power.

Name: G. Arkveld Vambraces
Description:
Guardian Arkveld armguards.
Instills the desire to tear at
friend and foe alike.

Name: G. Arkveld Coil
Description:
Guardian Arkveld waistgear.
The chains writhe subtly, eager
to ensnare prey.

Name: G. Arkveld Greaves
Description:
Guardian Arkveld leg armor.
Their power grows with each
relentless, hungry step.

Armguards made from Yian
Kut-Ku materials. The

Traditional chest armor with a
unique plating of intricately
pieced together monster bones.

Name: Bone Vambraces α
Description:
Traditional armguards made
from monster bones. It's a
wonder these mismatched
shapes fit together.

Name: Bone Coil α
Description:
Traditional waistgear bound
with monster bones. Looks
crude, but it does the job.

Name: Bone Greaves α
Description:
Traditional leg armor crafted
from monster bones so light it's
like wearing nothing at all.

Name: Alloy Helm α
Description:
A helmet crafted from quality
ore. While it doesn't look like
much, this is highly functional
armor.

Name: Alloy Mail α
Description:
Chest armor crafted from
quality ore. Made with a
logical, no-frills construction
that puts mobility first.

Name: Alloy Vambraces α
Description:
Armguards crafted from quality
ore. Every element is streamlined
for maximum utility.

Name: Alloy Coil α
Description:
Waistgear crafted from quality
ore. The complexly shaded patina
and sleek design are quite
stunning.

Name: Alloy Greaves α
Description:
Leg armor crafted from quality
ore. What it lacks in charm it
more than makes up in defense.

Name: Quematrice Helm α
Description:
Head armor made from Quematrice
spoils. The shock of feathers
ties the whole look together.

Name: Quematrice Mail α
Description:
Quematrice chest armor. The
design may look ceremonial,
but it offers ample protection.

Name: Quematrice Braces α
Description:

Name: Quematrice Coil α
Description:

Name: Quematrice Greaves α
Description:
Quematrice leg armor. The
ornate gaiters let a hunter
strut like a Quematrice.
